✨3 tips for hosting at home art party✨

Add Big Bend National Park @bigbendnps in West Texas to your travel bucket list & SAVE this post!! 🌄🌵🏜️Big Bend is 800,000+ acres of mountainous desert with 150+ miles of hiking trails. My kids love trails that lead to water 💦, so pack your swim suit, sunscreen, hat, and lots of water!👙☀️

✨5 DON’T MISS BIG BEND ADVENTURES W/ KIDS✨

1. Explore the Santa Elena Canyon🏞️
2. Play in Hot Springs & Rio Grande River🐴 
3. Fossil Discovery Exhibit 🦖🦕
4. Have lunch in Boquillas, Mexico (Bring passports!)🇲🇽 
5. Hike the Lost Mine Trail

And don’t forget to grab a Jr. Ranger book from any one of the 5 Visitors Centers in Big Bend. Kids can earn (free) embroidered patches for completing trails & activities! For lodging, we stayed at the @starlodgetx & loved it 💛☀️✨#bigbendnationalpark #bigbendnps

Questions? Leave ‘em in the comments!

☀️💦LOST CREEK TRAIL💦☀️ 

The Lost Creek trail is our favorite Austin hike. It ends in a gorgeous waterfall and swimming hole with a rock beach. Things to know about the Lost Creek Trail:

〰️It’s a 1.2 miles (round trip)📍
〰️ You start the trail under a bridge (Google Lost Creek Greenbelt Entrance) 🌳
〰️Wear water shoes (or be prepared to get sneakers wet)💦
〰️Trail is mostly shaded, but bring bug spray 🦟
〰️There is a fee on the weekends ($10 per person, $5 per dog, cc only)☀️🐶

✨ Save this trail for a magical hike with the kids this summer! ✨

🦬YELLOWSTONE & TETONS🌋

15 things you can’t miss in Yellowstone & Grand Tetons National Parks:

*SAVE & SHARE THIS REEL*

🌋YELLOWSTONE NATIONAL PARK🌋

1. Old Faithful 
2. Steamboat Geyser (Largest Geyser in the world!)
3. See the Grand Prismatic 🌋 
4. Artist Point in the Canyons 🎨 
5. Spy bear, bison & elk in Lamar Valley 🦬🦌🐻 
6. Hike Paint Pot trail for mud pots
7. Complete Jr. Ranger Books ✏️ 
8. Explore Mammoth Hot Springs
9. Picnic at Lake Yellowstone 🧺 
10. Pull off the main road for “side attractions” often! 🏞️ 💦 

🌌TETONS NATIONAL PARK🏞️

11. Swim in String Lake 💦 
12. Hike to Hidden Falls
13. Happy hour at Lake Jackson Lodge 🥂 
14. Eat & play at Leeks Pizzeria 🍕
15. Swim at Coulter Bay Beach 🏖️ 

Let me know if you have any questions in the comments!

🎨✨ *Wonderspace Austin*✨🎨

Explore 17 interactive art exhibits with the family at  @wonderspacesaustin! The exhibits change regularly. My 7 year olds favorites on this trip were…

〰️ “Rules” A giant collaborative tape canvas
〰️ “Body Paint” 🌈 
〰️ “Submergence” 8,000 hanging lights you can walk through 

Adult tickets are $24, kid tickets are $15, kids 3 and under are free! 

PRO TIP: Book the earliest time on a weekday! That’s what we did and we had it almost to ourselves!

👻 Looking for a fun, family friendly Halloween event this October? 🎃@pumpkinnights is back at Pioneer Farms in east Austin and better than ever! Wander the half mile walking path and explore 7 magical 🎃 lands including Neon Reef and Forbidden City! 🐡🕯️🐉 

What to expect:

~Pumpkin Nights is not scary (No jump scares or gore.)
~ Fire dancers happen every hour 🔥
~Parking is $10 🚗 
~Bring a stroller or wagon that can handle a dirt trail for your littles
